description:
Add proper error handling to this async function that fetches a user from an API. The current version has no error handling:

async function fetchUser(userId: string): Promise<User> {
  const response = await fetch(`https://api.example.com/users/${userId}`);
  const data = await response.json();
  return data;
}

Add error handling that: checks if response.ok is false and throws an error with the status code, wraps the entire function in try/catch, logs the error, and re-throws it.

Output ONLY the raw code. No explanations, no markdown formatting, no commentary. Just the code.
